[DhtmlXQ_comment0]mg fork 03||Another relatively simple diagram explaining the use of the fork.||Red has the initiative in this game but he is disadvantaged material wise. There is no immediate threat for checkmate for red, so he tries to gain material...[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
[DhtmlXQ_comment1]By taking the black cannon, red forces the black chariot where it wants to be![/DhtmlXQ_comment1]
[DhtmlXQ_comment2]If black refused this exchange, he would lose a cannon and be faced with the difficulty of trying to defend against a possible mate with the two chariots attacking this flank.[/DhtmlXQ_comment2]
[DhtmlXQ_comment3]Fork!||A black chariot is definitely lost now. Red goes into the endgame with relatively equivalent material, but superior pawns and positioning.[/DhtmlXQ_comment3]
[DhtmlXQ_comment5]One runs away, and the other is caught.[/DhtmlXQ_comment5]
